# Vibe coding (itin)

Before writing or changing code:

1. Read [AGENTS.md](../../AGENTS.md) and [docs/ai/TODO.md](../../docs/ai/TODO.md).
2. Skim [docs/ai/LEARNINGS.md](../../docs/ai/LEARNINGS.md) — rules from past corrections.
3. Read today's file in [docs/standups/](../../docs/standups/) (`YYYY-MM-DD.md`).

After meaningful work:

- Update [docs/ai/TODO.md](../../docs/ai/TODO.md) (move items to **Done** when finished).
- Add bullets to today's standup under the relevant name.

If the user corrected a mistake: follow [learn-from-feedback.mdc](learn-from-feedback.mdc) and update [LEARNINGS.md](../../docs/ai/LEARNINGS.md).

Conventions: Bun monorepo, Biome lint, `bun typecheck` before done. Do not commit unless the user asks. No secrets in git.
